article.headline: East Tenn. St. 85, Austin Peay 81
article.story: JOHNSON CITY, Tenn. (AP) -- Tim Smith scored 29 points and East Tennessee State held on to beat Austin Peay 85-81 on Saturday. ETSU (9-16) led 55-32 at halftime after shooting 73 percent from the floor in the first half. The Governors (11-16) trailed by as many as 30 in the first half before chipping away in the second. Anthony Davis hit a 3-pointer to make it 84-81 with 44 seconds left, but Levi Carmichael missed a 3-pointer that would have tied the game with 20 seconds remaining. James Anthony hit 1 of 2 free throws for the final margin and finished with 24 points. Austin Peay was led in scoring by Zac Schlader with 27. Maurice Hampton added 24 and Davis 18.
